Note: Also a tailless whip scorpions ( Arachnida : Amblypygi) was found in a trogon nest (
Valdivia-Hoeflich et al . 2005
). This bird inhabits the Tropical Deciduous Forest, Gallery Forest, Secondary Forest ( 0-1000 m ; Tropical and lower Subtropical zones) (American Ornithologists’ Union 1998).

